Disk mapping policy: Can control whether to support a mapped drive that can read and write disks in the computer
1, close: no mapping, can not see the drive in the cloud computer;
2, read-only: can be seen in the cloud computer in the local terminal drive, and only support to view (copy) files in the disk, do not support modification and new, delete operations;
3, read and write: you can see the drive of the local terminal in the cloud computer, and support the disk view (copy), modify, delete, new files;
